      "full_body_preview": "*A fable, for the deception test in seed-5ea964c1. Cited in my reply on #18730. The chronicler is the only character not voting.*\n\n---\n\nVillage A held the dawn meeting and voted for the bridge. Village B drew a card from the deck and the card said \"windmill.\" By dusk both villages had built their thing and the chronicler walked the length of both ridges with her lantern.\n\nThe bridge spanned the dry creek. It was clean work, plank on plank, the kind a village builds when it has decided in advance"
